[{"location":"#ParetoEfficiency.jl-Documentation","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","text":"A simple Julia package to calculate the Pareto front of a set of points.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","text":"This package only exports one function:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","text":"ParetoEfficiency.pareto_front\nParetoEfficiency.dominates\nParetoEfficiency.is_pareto_optimal","category":"page"},{"location":"#ParetoEfficiency.pareto_front","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.pareto_front","text":"pareto_front(X)\n\nReturns indices i[1], i[2], ..., i[K] of the Pareto optimal points. Here X is a cost matrix, with the costs of point i along the row X[i,:].\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ParetoEfficiency.dominates","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.dominates","text":"dominates(x, y)\n\nReturns true if costs x dominate costs y in the Pareto sense.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ParetoEfficiency.is_pareto_optimal","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.is_pareto_optimal","text":"is_pareto_optimal(i, X)\n\nReturns true if point i is Pareto optimal. Here X is a cost matrix, and the costs of a point j are along the row X[j,:].\n\n\n\n\n\nis_pareto_optimal(i, xs...)\n\nReturns true if point i is Pareto optimal. Here xs are cost vectors. The costs of point i are the list [x[i] for x in xs].\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Example","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","title":"ParetoEfficiency.jl Documentation","text":"using ParetoEfficiency, CairoMakie\n\nN = 1000\nX = randn(N, 2)\n\nfig = Figure(resolution=(800, 500))\nax = Axis(fig[1,1])\nscatter!(ax, X[:,1], X[:,2], color=:black, markersize=4)\n\np = pareto_front(X[:,1], X[:,2])\nlines!(ax, X[p,1], X[p,2], label=\"pareto(+,+)\", color=:red)\n\np = pareto_front(-X[:,1], X[:,2])\nlines!(ax, X[p,1], X[p,2], label=\"pareto(-,+)\", color=:blue)\n\np = pareto_front(X[:,1], -X[:,2])\nlines!(ax, X[p,1], X[p,2], label=\"pareto(+,-)\", color=:orange)\n\np = pareto_front(-X[:,1], -X[:,2])\nlines!(ax, X[p,1], X[p,2], label=\"pareto(-,-)\", color=:green)\n\nLegend(fig[1,2], ax)\n\nfig","category":"page"}]
